## Problem
In spawnTakeChild() (terminal-manager.ts:1089), the take-loop unconditionally calls takeSendUserTurn() to send the prompt via stdin, regardless of agent dialect. For codex agents (non-interactive), stdin is set to 'ignore' and takeStdinClosed is initialized to true, so takeSendUserTurn() always returns false, causing every take iteration after the first to immediately fail with:

```
Failed to send prompt for take iteration N
✗ Process exited with code 1
```

## Root Cause
Commit a59b703 fixed the initial session prompt (line 1448) by wrapping it in if (isInteractive), but the same pattern was not applied to the take-loop iteration code at line 1089.

For codex agents, the prompt is already passed as a CLI argument via buildPromptModeArgs() at line 871, so stdin send is unnecessary.

## Suggested Fix
Wrap the stdin send in spawnTakeChild with an effectiveIsInteractive guard, matching the pattern used for the initial prompt:

```typescript
// terminal-manager.ts ~line 1089
if (effectiveIsInteractive) {
  const sent = takeSendUserTurn(takePrompt, `take_${takeIteration}`);
  if (!sent) {
    takeCloseInput();
    pushEvent({ type: 'stderr', data: `Failed to send prompt...`, timestamp: Date.now() });
    takeChild.kill('SIGTERM');
    entry.process = null;
    finishSession(1);
  }
}
```

## Files
- src/lib/terminal-manager.ts (lines 852-1097)
